title: Cable High Pulley Overhead Tricep Extension

items: Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent.
Grasp the rope attachment with both hands and bring it behind your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears.
Extend your arms upward, fully straightening your elbows and contracting your triceps.
Slowly lower the rope back behind your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears and maintaining control of the weight.
Repeat for desired number of reps.
Targets the triceps muscles, helping to build strength and definition in the back of the arms
Engages the core muscles for stability and balance during the exercise
Allows for a full range of motion, stretching and contracting the triceps muscles for optimal muscle growth
Can be easily adjusted for different fitness levels by changing the weight or resistance on the cable machine
Can be performed with a variety of grip positions to target different areas of the triceps muscles
